ow post byline (post author, post published date, and category) or post meta data with link.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"http://smallenvelop.com/show-post-byline-with-link-to-author-post-and-category-archive/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"http://smallenvelop.com/show-post-byline-with-link-to-author-post-and-category-archive/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 17 May 2015 20:04:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How to\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"meta\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://smallenvelop.com/?p=1403\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:648:\"<p>WordPress blog posts have meta informations or post byline which is called as post meta data. You can find these post bylines around the title, either above or below. What is Post meta data. The .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/show-post-byline-with-link-to-author-post-and-category-archive/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/show-post-byline-with-link-to-author-post-and-category-archive/\">Show post byline (post author, post published date, and category) or post meta data with link.</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6701:\"<p>WordPress blog posts have meta informations or post byline which is called as post meta data. You can find these post bylines around the title, either above or below.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/post-by-line-post-meta-data1.jpg\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-1405 aligncenter\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/post-by-line-post-meta-data1.jpg\" alt=\"post byline or post meta data with link\" width=\"800\" height=\"339\" /></a></p>\n<h2>What is Post meta data.</h2>\n<p>The post meta informations consist of post author name, post category and post published date and comments count for each post. These meta informations can be linked with archive pages ( Author archives, Month archives, Category archive ). Showing post meta data in your post is a good practice which help people to get these informations and better navigation to post archives.</p>\n<h3>How to show post byline with link.</h3>\n<blockquote><p>Author name:</p></blockquote>\n<p></p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">&lt;?php the_author_posts_link(); ?&gt;</pre><p>the_author_post_link() outputs author name with an anchor to author archive page. All the posts by this author is listed on the author archive page.</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">&lt;a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/author/poonam/\" title=\"Posts by poonam\" rel=\"author\"&gt;poonam&lt;/a&gt;</pre><p></p>\n<blockquote><p>Post published date:</p></blockquote>\n<p></p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">&lt;?php \r\n $archive_year  = get_the_time(\'Y\'); \r\n $archive_month = get_the_time(\'m\'); \r\n $archive_day   = get_the_time(\'d\'); \r\n?&gt;\r\n&lt;a href=\"&lt;?php echo get_day_link( $archive_year, $archive_month, $archive_day); ?&gt;\"&gt;&lt;?php echo get_the_time(\'M d, Y\') ?&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</pre><p>In the above code echo get_day_link ( $archive_year, $archive_month, $archive_day ); would output a URL which links to month archive. And the code echo get_the_time(&#8216;M d, Y&#8217;) outputs the date. The string &#8216;M d  Y&#8217; creates a date that look like this: May 18 2015.</p>\n<p>You can use the following <a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Formatting_Date_and_Time\" target=\"_blank\">Formatting Date and Time in WordPress</a>. Here is what each format character in the string above represents:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>l</code> = Full name for day of the week (lower-case L).</li>\n<li><code>F</code> = Full name for the month.</li>\n<li><code>j</code> = The day of the month.</li>\n<li><code>Y</code> = The year in 4 digits. (lower-case y gives the year&#8217;s last 2 digits)</li>\n</ul>\n<table class=\"widefat\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\">Day of Month</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d</td>\n<td>Numeric, with leading zeros</td>\n<td>01–31</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>j</td>\n<td>Numeric, without leading zeros</td>\n<td>1–31</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>The English suffix for the day of the month</td>\n<td>st, nd or th in the 1st, 2nd or 15th.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\">Weekday</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>l</td>\n<td>Full name  (lowercase &#8216;L&#8217;)</td>\n<td>Sunday – Saturday</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>D</td>\n<td>Three letter name</td>\n<td>Mon – Sun</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\">Month</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>m</td>\n<td>Numeric, with leading zeros</td>\n<td>01–12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>n</td>\n<td>Numeric, without leading zeros</td>\n<td>1–12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>F</td>\n<td>Textual full</td>\n<td>January – December</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>M</td>\n<td>Textual three letters</td>\n<td>Jan &#8211; Dec</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\">Year</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Y</td>\n<td>Numeric, 4 digits</td>\n<td>Eg., 1999, 2003</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>y</td>\n<td>Numeric, 2 digits</td>\n<td>Eg., 99, 03</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>a</td>\n<td>Lowercase</td>\n<td>am, pm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>A</td>\n<td>Uppercase</td>\n<td>AM, PM</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>g</td>\n<td>Hour, 12-hour, without leading zeros</td>\n<td>1–12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>h</td>\n<td>Hour, 12-hour, with leading zeros</td>\n<td>01–12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>G</td>\n<td>Hour, 24-hour, without leading zeros</td>\n<td>0-23</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>H</td>\n<td>Hour, 24-hour, with leading zeros</td>\n<td>00-23</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>i</td>\n<td>Minutes, with leading zeros</td>\n<td>00-59</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>s</td>\n<td>Seconds, with leading zeros</td>\n<td>00-59</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>Timezone abbreviation</td>\n<td>Eg., EST, MDT &#8230;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\">Full Date/Time</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>c</td>\n<td>ISO 8601</td>\n<td>2004-02-12T15:19:21+00:00</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>r</td>\n<td><a class=\"external mw-magiclink-rfc\" href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2822\">RFC 2822</a></td>\n<td>Thu, 21 Dec 2000 16:01:07 +0200</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<blockquote><p>Post category :</p></blockquote>\n<p></p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">&lt;?php echo get_the_category_list(\', \'); ?&gt;</pre><p>get_the_category_list(&#8216;, &#8216;) shows all the categories the post is assigned to, in unordered list with comma seperated links to archive. For example:</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">&lt;ul class=\"post-categories\"&gt;\r\n &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/category/wordpress-basics/\" rel=\"category tag\"&gt;How to&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;/li&gt;\r\n &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/category/theme-customization/\" rel=\"category tag\"&gt;Theme Customization&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;</pre><p></p>\n<blockquote><p>Comment count :</p></blockquote>\n<p></p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">&lt;?php comments_number( \'no responses\', \'one response\', \'% responses\' ); ?&gt;</pre><p>In the above code % show number of comments in the posts, if it&#8217;s not 0 or 1. If there is no comments it will simply echo &#8216;no responses&#8217;, if there is only one comment it will echo one response.</p>\n<p>You can replace the word &#8216; No responses&#8217;, &#8216;one response&#8217; and &#8216;responses&#8217; in the third argument and leave the &#8216;%&#8217; as it is.</p>\n<blockquote><p>Post modified date :</p></blockquote>\n<p>Sometimes we need to show when the post was updated and modified so that the visitors may be aware of the new contents added to that post.</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">Last modified &lt;?php the_modified_time(\'F j, Y\'); ?&gt; // &lt;?php the_modified_time(\'g:i a\'); ?&gt;</pre><p>It will output the following: Last modified May 17, 2015 // 10:56 am</p>\n<p>Hope this article may be helpful to you. Leave comments.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/show-post-byline-with-link-to-author-post-and-category-archive/\">Show post byline (post author, post published date, and category) or post meta data with link.</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"http://smallenvelop.com/show-post-byline-with-link-to-author-post-and-category-archive/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"4 ways to limit post excerpt length in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://smallenvelop.com/4-ways-to-limit-post-excerpt-length-in-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"http://smallenvelop.com/4-ways-to-limit-post-excerpt-length-in-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 29 Apr 2015 10:05:29 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How to\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Theme Customization\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"limit post excerpt\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"post excerpt\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"post summary\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"http://smallenvelop.com/blog/?p=698\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:571:\"<p>Updated: A post excerpt is a description or post summary. When we don&#8217;t want to show the full content we uses post excerpt. It is mainly used in following ways in a WordPress theme. RSS .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/4-ways-to-limit-post-excerpt-length-in-wordpress/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/4-ways-to-limit-post-excerpt-length-in-wordpress/\">4 ways to limit post excerpt length in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6012:\"<p>Updated:<br />\nA post excerpt is a description or post summary. When we don&#8217;t want to show the full content we uses post excerpt. It is mainly used in following ways in a WordPress theme.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>RSS Feeds</li>\n<li>Search results</li>\n<li>Tag archives</li>\n<li>Category archives</li>\n<li>Monthly archives</li>\n<li>Author archives</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To show a post summary simply use the_excerpt() below post title. By default WordPress show a limit of 55 words in an excerpt. However you can customize this limit in many ways.</p>\n<h2>In this post I will show you a number of ways to limit post excerpt length.</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Limit post excerpt length or post content length using number of words.</li>\n<li>Limiting excerpt length to number of characters.</li>\n<li>Limit post summary by adding &#8216;read more&#8217; tag.</li>\n<li>Enabling custom excerpt to write you own summary for each post.</li>\n<li>Control Excerpt Length using Filters</li>\n</ol>\n<blockquote><p>Let&#8217;s learn how to customize or your post summary using word count and characters count.</p></blockquote>\n<h3>1. Limit post excerpt length and content length using number of words.</h3>\n<p>Add following code in your function.php file.</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">function excerpt($limit) {\r\n  $excerpt = explode(\' \', get_the_excerpt(), $limit);\r\n  if (count($excerpt)&gt;=$limit) {\r\n    array_pop($excerpt);\r\n    $excerpt = implode(\" \",$excerpt).\'...\';\r\n  } else {\r\n    $excerpt = implode(\" \",$excerpt);\r\n  }	\r\n  $excerpt = preg_replace(\'`\\[[^\\]]*\\]`\',\'\',$excerpt);\r\n  return $excerpt;\r\n}\r\n \r\nfunction content($limit) {\r\n  $content = explode(\' \', get_the_content(), $limit);\r\n  if (count($content)&gt;=$limit) {\r\n    array_pop($content);\r\n    $content = implode(\" \",$content).\'...\';\r\n  } else {\r\n    $content = implode(\" \",$content);\r\n  }	\r\n  $content = preg_replace(\'/\\[.+\\]/\',\'\', $content);\r\n  $content = apply_filters(\'the_content\', $content); \r\n  $content = str_replace(\']]&gt;\', \']]&amp;gt;\', $content);\r\n  return $content;\r\n}</pre><p>Now, in every place where you use <code>the_excerpt()</code> or <code>the_content()</code> in your loop, use <code>excerpt($limit)</code> or <code>content($limit)</code>.</p>\n<p>For example if you want to limit your excerpt length to 30 words use<code> echo excerpt(30) </code> and for content.<br />\nSource: <a href=\"http://bavotasan.com/2009/limiting-the-number-of-words-in-your-excerpt-or-content-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">Bavotasan</a></p>\n<h3>2. Limiting excerpt length to number of characters.</h3>\n<p>Sometimes you want to limit the post excerpt limit on character and not by words. You just want to limit the character length in excerpt.</p>\n<p>Here is the solution. Add the following code to your <code>function.php</code> file</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">function get_excerpt(){\r\n$excerpt = get_the_content();\r\n$excerpt = preg_replace(\" (\\[.*?\\])\",\'\',$excerpt);\r\n$excerpt = strip_shortcodes($excerpt);\r\n$excerpt = strip_tags($excerpt);\r\n$excerpt = substr($excerpt, 0, 50);\r\n$excerpt = substr($excerpt, 0, strripos($excerpt, \" \"));\r\n$excerpt = trim(preg_replace( \'/\\s+/\', \' \', $excerpt));\r\n$excerpt = $excerpt.\'... &lt;a href=\"\'.$permalink.\'\"&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;\';\r\nreturn $excerpt;\r\n}</pre><p>You can change the length 50 to your desired character length. And also &#8216;more&#8217; to what text you want to display. Then call your function <code> echo get_excerpt(); </code> wherever you are planning on getting your posts.<br />\n<code><!--?php echo get_excerpt(); ?--></code></p>\n<h3>3. Limit post summary by adding <code>read more</code> tag.</h3>\n<p>You can also set your excerpt length by adding <code>more</code> or <code>read more</code> tag using post editor tag option. Simply place the blinking text cursor where you want the excerpt to be stopped and click the &#8216;more&#8217; tag.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1323 size-large\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/insert-readmore-tag-to-limit-post-excerpt-length-1024x449.png\" alt=\"insert read more tag to limit post excerpt length\" width=\"640\" height=\"281\" /></p>\n<h3>4. Enabling custom excerpt to write you own summary for each post.</h3>\n<p>Sometimes you might not satisfied with automatically generated excerpt, which might be breaking your site layout.<br />\nThere is a feature in WordPress to show an additional field for custom excerpt. This feature isn&#8217;t activated by default but very simple to enable for any post. Click on Screen Option found above the title in post editor.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1324 size-large\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Enabling-Custom-Excerpts-to-limit-post-excerpt-1024x653.png\" alt=\"Enabling Custom Excerpts to limit post excerpt length\" width=\"640\" height=\"408\" /></p>\n<p>By enabling it there is a new field &#8216;excerpt&#8217; can be seen below the content editor, as you can see in the image above. Now enter your custom excerpt with your desired length to fit your site layout.</p>\n<h3>5. Control Excerpt Length using Filters</h3>\n<p>Excerpt length is set to 55 words by default. We can change this default value without overriding default the_excerpt() function, so that you don&#8217;t have to make a change in each files and templates where you have used the_excerpt().</p>\n<p>To change this default excerpt length to 20 words using excerpt_length filter, add the following code to functions.php file in your theme:</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">function custom_excerpt_length( $length ) {\r\n	return 20;\r\n}\r\nadd_filter( \'excerpt_length\', \'custom_excerpt_length\', 999 );</pre><p>This way you can limit post excerpts length.</p>\n<p>Hope this article may help you to limit post excerpt length. Comments are welcome.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/4-ways-to-limit-post-excerpt-length-in-wordpress/\">4 ways to limit post excerpt length in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"http://smallenvelop.com/4-ways-to-limit-post-excerpt-length-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"Best Free Page Builder Plugin WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"http://smallenvelop.com/best-free-page-builder-plugin-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://smallenvelop.com/best-free-page-builder-plugin-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 05 Apr 2015 17:22:03 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Best Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"best page builder plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"free page builder plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"page builder plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://smallenvelop.com/?p=1253\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:540:\"<p>Today most of the premium WordPress themes comes with page builder and drag n drop features to design custom layout. But what if you use free themes? Here I listed down the best free page .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/best-free-page-builder-plugin-wordpress/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/best-free-page-builder-plugin-wordpress/\">Best Free Page Builder Plugin WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7491:\"<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Today most of the premium WordPress themes comes with page builder and drag n drop features to design custom layout. But what if you use free themes?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Here I listed down the best free page builder plugins for WordPress. With these plugins you can make awesome sites with custom pages.</span></p>\n<h2>Best Free Page Builder Plugin for WordPress</h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"> <a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/page-builder-by-siteorigin.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1269 size-full\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/page-builder-by-siteorigin.jpg\" alt=\"Page Builder by SiteOrigin free page builder plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"247\" /></a></span></span></p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\">1. </span><strong><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><a title=\"Page Builder by SiteOrigin Free Drag n drop WordPress Plugin\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/siteorigin-panels/\" target=\"_blank\">Page Builder by SiteOrigin</a></span></strong></span></h3>\n<p>Page Builder by SiteOrigin is the most popular page creation, layout builder plugin for WordPress. It is easy to build responsive grid-based page content that adapts to mobile devices with pixel perfect accuracy.</p>\n<p>SiteOrigin comes with a simple drag and drop interface means you&#8217;ll never need to touch a line of code. This plugin integrates with any theme. This capability guarantees that your content will always come along with you, even when your design tastes change. SiteOrigin Widgets Bundle give you all the most common widgets  you need.</p>\n<div class=\"video-container\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/114529361\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" title=\"Page Builder 2 Overview\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<a class=\"btn btn-default btn-lg  \" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/siteorigin-panels/\"  target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-download\" ></i> Download</a>\n<hr />\n<p><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1268 size-full\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/MiniMax-Page-Layout-Builder.jpg\" alt=\"MiniMax – Page Layout Builder free page builder plugin for WordPress\" width=\"767\" height=\"248\" /></span></p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\">2. </span><strong><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><a title=\"MiniMax - Page Layout Builder free page builder plugin\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/page-layout-builder\" target=\"_blank\">MiniMax &#8211; Page Layout Builder</a></span></strong></h3>\n<p>Building custom WordPress page layout using Page Layout Builder is just as easy as drag-and-drop. This plugin also compatible with any theme and  packaged with special options for building squeeze pages with all necessary modules. You can build a landing page within minutes. you can also export your page layout and import it to another site with minimax just in few clicks. No need to build same layout repeatedly.</p>\n<p><span class=\'embed-youtube\' style=\'text-align:center; display: block;\'><iframe class=\'youtube-player\' type=\'text/html\' width=\'640\' height=\'390\' src=\'http://www.youtube.com/embed/iPQAYdP2kyI?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;fs=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;wmode=transparent\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen=\'true\'></iframe></span><br />\n&nbsp;<br />\n<a class=\"btn btn-default btn-lg  \" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/page-layout-builder/\"  target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-download\" ></i> Download</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1271\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Aqua-Page-Builder.jpg\" alt=\"Aqua Page Builder Free WordPress Plugin\" width=\"770\" height=\"249\" /></span></p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\">3. <strong><a title=\"Aqua Page Builder Free WordPress layout builder plugin\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/aqua-page-builder/\" target=\"_blank\">Aqua Page Builder</a></strong></span></h3>\n<p>Aqua Page Builder is a powerful WordPress plugin that allows you to create an unlimited number of template variations for use in your WordPress themes. It follows the same user interface used by the Menus &amp; Widgets admin pages &#8211; making you feel right at home with the UI.</p>\n<a class=\"btn btn-default btn-lg  \" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/aqua-page-builder/\"  target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-download\" ></i> Download</a>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1270\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Page-Builder-by-WooRockets.com_.jpg\" alt=\"Page Builder by WooRockets.com free layout builder wordpress plugin\" width=\"770\" height=\"248\" /><br />\n4. </span><strong><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><a title=\"WR Page Builder Plugin Free\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wr-pagebuilder\" target=\"_blank\">WR Page Builder</a></span></strong></h3>\n<p>WR Page Builder is a simple Drag and Drop page builder designed with an intuitive interface, simple and extremely easy to use, this plugin gives a new experience for building pages and creating an entire online shop by visual drag-and-drop functionality.</p>\n<a class=\"btn btn-default btn-lg  \" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wr-pagebuilder/\"  target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-download\" ></i> Download</a>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1267\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Beaver-Builder-WordPress-Page-Builder.jpg\" alt=\"Beaver Builder WordPress free Page Builder plugin\" width=\"770\" height=\"248\" /></span></p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\">5. </span><strong><span style=\"color: #d74d2f;\"><a title=\"Beaver Builder free page layout builder plugin\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/beaver-builder-lite-version/\" target=\"_blank\">Beaver Builder</a></span></strong></h3>\n<p>Beaver Builder is a drag and drop page builder that works on the frontend of WordPress and allows you to create beautiful layouts without having to write any code. Beaver Builder up with a comprehensive set of content modules to aid you in building stunning layouts within an intuitive drag and drop system. In addition to content modules, Beaver Builder also supports core and third party WordPress widgets and shortcodes.</p>\n<div class=\"video-container\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/122546221\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" title=\"Beaver Builder Designers Video\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<a class=\"btn btn-default btn-lg  \" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/beaver-builder-lite-version/\"  target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-download\" ></i> Download</a>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can also check our article on best  drag and drop page builder themes <a title=\"themes\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/top-10-wordpress-dragndrop-page-builder-theme/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Please let me know what do you think! Do you use any of the plugins listed? How is it? Or did I miss a must have plugin? Please let me know!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/best-free-page-builder-plugin-wordpress/\">Best Free Page Builder Plugin WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://smallenvelop.com/best-free-page-builder-plugin-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"How to Create Featured Posts Section in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"http://smallenvelop.com/how-to-create-featured-posts-in-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"http://smallenvelop.com/how-to-create-featured-posts-in-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 28 Mar 2015 15:30:05 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How to\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Theme Customization\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"featured post widget\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"featured posts\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://smallenvelop.com/?p=1193\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:609:\"<p>WordPress is well known for its great powerful customization feature. Whenever you feel something is required, you can easily achieve that in many ways such as: WordPress plugins Adding functions Editing previously created functions. Here we .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/how-to-create-featured-posts-in-wordpress/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/how-to-create-featured-posts-in-wordpress/\">How to Create Featured Posts Section in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5426:\"<p>WordPress is well known for its great powerful customization feature. Whenever you feel something is required, you can easily achieve that in many ways such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>WordPress plugins</li>\n<li>Adding functions</li>\n<li>Editing previously created functions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1244\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/featured-post.jpg\" alt=\"featured-post\" width=\"800\" height=\"350\" /></p>\n<p>Here we are going to learn how to add a featured posts section or featured content in your WordPress. Featured contents are used to highlight some content to your visitors. Sometimes it is mandatory to display some important posts first to your audience. So in this tutorial we&#8217;ll learn to make featured posts section.</p>\n<h2>Add a featured posts section</h2>\n<p>There is a simple step by step procedure to follow.</p>\n<p>Before we proceed we need a WordPress Installation with any theme. In this tutorial we are using &#8216;<a title=\"Bharat - A fast and responsive free blog WordPress  theme.\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/bharat/\" target=\"_blank\">Bharat</a>&#8216; a simple, beautiful and responsive blog theme.</p>\n<p>There are 3 steps for this procedure.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Creating a checkbox (metabox) in post/page admin area.</li>\n<li>Save meta box value.</li>\n<li>Display the featured posts on front.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Step 1- Creating a check-box</h4>\n<p>To add a checkbox to pages/posts edit screen add the following function to your theme&#8217;s functions.php file.</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">function register_post_assets(){\r\n    add_meta_box(\'featured-post\', __(\'Featured Post\'), \'add_featured_meta_box\', \'post\', \'advanced\', \'high\');\r\n}\r\nadd_action(\'admin_init\', \'register_post_assets\', 1);</pre><p></p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">function add_featured_meta_box($post){\r\n    $featured = get_post_meta($post-&gt;ID, \'_featured-post\', true);\r\n    echo \"&lt;label for=\'_featured-post\'&gt;\".__(\'Feature this post?\', \'bharat\').\"&lt;/label&gt;\";\r\n    echo \"&lt;input type=\'checkbox\' name=\'featured-post\' id=\'featured-post\' value=\'1\' \".checked(1, $featured).\" /&gt;\";\r\n}</pre><p>It will enable you to add posts to the featured content on the front page or any other page by simply checking the check box.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1243\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/featured-post-featured-content-in-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"featured post featured content in wordpress\" width=\"900\" height=\"345\" /></p>\n<h4>Step 2 &#8211; Save meta box value</h4>\n<p>We have done creating a check box in post/page edit screen. Now in this step we&#8217;ll create a function button to save or update the checkbox value. Add following code to your function.php file</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">function save_featured_meta($post_id){\r\n   if (isset($_REQUEST[\'featured-post\']))\r\n        update_post_meta(esc_attr($post_id), \'_featured-post\', esc_attr($_REQUEST[\'featured-post\'])); \r\n        }\r\nadd_action(\'save_post\', \'save_featured_meta\');</pre><p>The <a title=\"Function update_post_meta WordPress codex\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Function_Reference/update_post_meta\" target=\"_blank\">update posts meta</a> function will update or save the data to the database of a meta key &#8216;featured-post&#8217;.</p>\n<h4>Step 3- Displaying the Featured Posts on the Front</h4>\n<p>And the last step is to output the featured post. To display the featured posts make a <a title=\"Page Templates WordPress Codex\" href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Page_Templates\" target=\"_blank\">page template</a> in your themes directory  and add the below code</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">&lt;?php\r\n  $args = array(\r\n        \'posts_per_page\' =&gt; 5,\r\n        \'meta_key\' =&gt; \'_featured-post\',\r\n        \'meta_value\' =&gt; 1\r\n    );\r\n    $featured = new WP_Query($args);\r\n \r\nif ($featured-&gt;have_posts()): while($featured-&gt;have_posts()): $featured-&gt;the_post(); ?&gt;\r\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href=\"&lt;?php the_permalink(); ?&gt;\"&gt; &lt;?php the_title(); ?&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=\"details\"&gt;By &lt;a href=\"&lt;?php the_author_posts() ?&gt;\"&gt;&lt;?php the_author(); ?&gt; &lt;/a&gt; / On &lt;?php echo get_the_date(\'F j, Y\'); ?&gt; / In &lt;?php the_category(\', \'); ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;?php if (has_post_thumbnail()) : ?&gt;\r\n \r\n&lt;figure&gt; &lt;a href=\"&lt;?php the_permalink(); ?&gt;\"&gt;&lt;?php the_post_thumbnail(\'\', array(\'class\' =&gt; \'box\')); ?&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/figure&gt;\r\n&lt;p &gt;&lt;?php the_excerpt();?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;?php\r\nendif;\r\nendwhile; else:\r\nendif;\r\n?&gt;</pre><p>You can also make your posts featured using Free WordPress plugins.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Advance featured post widget free wordpress plugin\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-featured-post-widget/\" target=\"_blank\">Advance Featured Post Widget</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Featured Post Free WordPress Plugin\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/featured-post/\" target=\"_blank\">Featured Post</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Hope this will help you make your theme featured content or featured post compatible. Please do Comments if you have any queries.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/how-to-create-featured-posts-in-wordpress/\">How to Create Featured Posts Section in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"http://smallenvelop.com/how-to-create-featured-posts-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"How To Add Language Translator To WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-language-translator-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-language-translator-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 11 Mar 2015 17:00:16 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Best Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How to\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"language translate\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"translator\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"wpml\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://smallenvelop.com/?p=1177\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:572:\"<p>In this world people speak many languages, people of different areas have their different mother tongue. Every country has its own national language. English is a global language but people from different areas prefer different .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-language-translator-wordpress/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-language-translator-wordpress/\">How To Add Language Translator To WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2851:\"<p>In this world people speak many languages, people of different areas have their different mother tongue. Every country has its own national language. English is a global language but people from different areas prefer different languages, So if your website is restricted to only one language you can miss the chance to link large audience.</p>\n<p>Generally for any language translation we simply use <a href=\"https://translate.google.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Google Translate</a> to translate the site over to our desired language. In this article we will show you how to add language translate to WordPress.</p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #ff9900;\"> How to Add Language Translator to WordPress </span></h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Download and activate the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/google-language-translator/\" target=\"_blank\">Google Language Translator </a>plugin from WordPress repository.</li>\n<li>After activating the plugin go to <strong>Settings » Google Language Translator</strong> to configure the plugin.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1178\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/google-language-translate-1024x425.png\" alt=\"google-language-translate\" width=\"640\" height=\"266\" /></p>\n<p>Here you will make sure that the check box next to plugin status is checked this is responsible for plugin activation. After that you will  select default language of your website and translation languages in which you want to convert your site.</p>\n<p>Here you can also choose the setting for show flag images, show translate box, layout option and many other options.</p>\n<p>This plugin provide a shortcode &#8220;<span style=\"color: #993300;\">[google-translator]</span>&#8221; which you can use in your post/page or sidebar. For display the language translate in your header/footer or page template you can use the following code<br />\n<span style=\"color: #993300;\">&lt;?php echo do_shortcode(&#8216;[google-translator]&#8217;); ?&gt;   </span></p>\n<p>You can also use google translate widget directly in your sidebar.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-1181\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/google-translate-flag.png\" alt=\"google translate-flag\" width=\"335\" height=\"206\" /><br />\n<a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/google-translate-dropdown.png\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-1180\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/google-translate-dropdown.png\" alt=\"google-translate-dropdown\" width=\"225\" height=\"188\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-language-translator-wordpress/\">How To Add Language Translator To WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-language-translator-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"Customize WordPress Login Page With WordPress Customizer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"http://smallenvelop.com/customize-wordpress-login-page-with-wordpress-customizer/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://smallenvelop.com/customize-wordpress-login-page-with-wordpress-customizer/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 11 Feb 2015 17:36:54 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How to\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"login customizer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"theme customizer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://smallenvelop.com/?p=1066\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:682:\"<p>The Theme Customization API, added in WordPress 3.4. This API provides ease to developers to customize and add controls to the &#8220;Appearance&#8221;, &#8220;Customize&#8221; admin screen. The Theme Customization screen (i.e. &#8220;Theme Customizer&#8221;) allows site admins .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/customize-wordpress-login-page-with-wordpress-customizer/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/customize-wordpress-login-page-with-wordpress-customizer/\">Customize WordPress Login Page With WordPress Customizer</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2394:\"<p>The Theme Customization API, added in WordPress 3.4. This API provides ease to developers to customize and add controls to the &#8220;Appearance&#8221;, &#8220;Customize&#8221; admin screen. The Theme Customization screen (i.e. &#8220;Theme Customizer&#8221;) allows site admins to alter a theme&#8217;s settings, color scheme or widgets, and see a preview of those changes in real time.</p>\n<h2>Use Custom Login Customizer plugin to customize WordPress login page</h2>\n<p>The Custom Login Customizer plugin uses Customization API and allows you to easily customize WordPress login page with WordPress Customizer !<br />\nAfter activation of the plugin, navigate to Appearance &gt; Login Customizer in order to launch your login page in the customizer.this plugin adds its own panel to the customizer with a numerous of options for customizing the design of your website’s login page.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/smallenvelop-login-customizer-1024x592.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-1127 size-large aligncenter\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/smallenvelop-login-customizer-1024x592-1024x592.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"370\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Features in Custom Login Customizer</h2>\n<p>1.  Add a login logo, defie width, height, and padding for logo.<br />\n2. Add a background image, select background color and define size.<br />\n3. Set a background for the form<br />\n4. Adjust form styling – width, height, padding, border<br />\n5. Style input field width, margin, background, and input/label colors<br />\n6. Color picker for button background, border, hover background/border, button box shadow.<br />\n7. Select text colors.<br />\n8. Add custom CSS.</p>\n<p>Use this plugin and easily customize WordPress login page with live preview and enjoy!!!</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t want to use plugin for customizing your WordPress login page you can also do it manually. Read our article<a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/customize-wordpress-registration-page/\" target=\"_blank\"> Customize WordPress Registration/Login Page</a>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/customize-wordpress-login-page-with-wordpress-customizer/\">Customize WordPress Login Page With WordPress Customizer</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://smallenvelop.com/customize-wordpress-login-page-with-wordpress-customizer/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"Add Custom Message on WordPress Login Page\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-custom-message-wordpress-login-page/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-custom-message-wordpress-login-page/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 31 Jan 2015 12:51:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Theme Customization\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"WP Login\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Customize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"login\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"login page customization\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://smallenvelop.com/?p=1032\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:586:\"<p>Adding a custom message in WordPress login page make your site more interactive to your visitors. We have learned to customize our WordPress Login/Registration page. Now we can change WordPress default logo with our own logo and .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-custom-message-wordpress-login-page/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-custom-message-wordpress-login-page/\">Add Custom Message on WordPress Login Page</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4812:\"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Adding a custom message in WordPress login page make your site more interactive to your visitors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We have learned to customize our WordPress Login/Registration page. Now we can change WordPress <a title=\"Customize WordPress Registration Page\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/customize-wordpress-registration-page/\" target=\"_blank\">default logo</a> with our own logo and add a nice background instead of WordPress default background. In this tutorial, we’ll learn how to customize our WordPress login page by adding custom  text or message on WordPress login page.</p>\n<h2>How to add custom message or text to WordPress login page</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To add a custom message on WordPress login page, we can use login_message filter.<br />\nThe filter &#8220;<a title=\"WordPress Codex - Login_Message\" href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Plugin_API/Filter_Reference/login_message\" target=\"_blank\">login message</a>&#8221; is used to filter the message displayed on the WordPress log in page above the log in form. This filter is used to return HTML markup.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Copy the below code and paste it into your theme&#8217;s functions.php file to add a custom message on WordPress login page</p>\n<p></p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">//* Add custom message to WordPress login page\r\n\r\nfunction smallenvelop_login_message( $message ) {\r\n    if ( empty($message) ){\r\n        return \"&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to SmallEnvelop. Please login to continue&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\";\r\n    } else {\r\n        return $message;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nadd_filter( \'login_message\', \'smallenvelop_login_message\' );</pre><p>Here you can see how it looks after adding the code. The text appears just below the logo. You can add some HTML and some CSS to style the text.<br />\n<a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/CustomMessage-.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1033 \" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/CustomMessage-.png\" alt=\"Custom wordpress login page message\" width=\"486\" height=\"495\" /></a></p>\n<p>Like the WordPress default login page you can also customize your WordPress admin dashboard. We’ve some more tutorial on creating a stunning admin dashboard. Check it out here.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"add custom dashboard widget\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/how-to-add-custom-dashboard-widgets-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">Add Custom Dashboard Widgets in WordPress</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"remove-unwanted-metaboxes-in-admin-panel\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/remove-unwanted-metaboxes-in-admin-panel/\" target=\"_blank\">Remove Unwanted Metaboxes or widgets in Admin Panel<br />\n</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can also use free WordPress plugins to customize your login page. These plugins can be found free on <a title=\"Free WordPress Plugins\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress plugin</a> repository. Here I have listed some of the free plugins you can use in your WordPress sites.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"WP Custom Login Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-custom-login/\" target=\"_blank\">WP Custom Login</a> Free WordPress Plugin</li>\n<li><a title=\"Sexy Login Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/sexy-login/\" target=\"_blank\">Sexy Login</a> Free WordPress Plugin</li>\n<li><a title=\"Memphis WordPress Custom Login\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/memphis-wordpress-custom-login/\" target=\"_blank\">Memphis Custom Login</a> Free WordPress Plugin</li>\n<li><a title=\"Branded Login Screen Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/branded-login-screen/\" target=\"_blank\">Branded Login Screen</a> Free WordPress Plugin</li>\n<li><a title=\"BM Custom Login Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/bm-custom-login/\" target=\"_blank\">BM Custom Login</a> Free WordPress Plugin</li>\n<li><a title=\"A5 Custom Login Page Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/custom-login-page/\" target=\"_blank\">A5 Custom Login Page</a> Free WordPress Plugin</li>\n<li><a title=\"Custom Login CSS Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-login-css/\" target=\"_blank\">Custom Login CSS</a> Free WordPress Plugin</li>\n<li><a title=\"My WordPress Login Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/my-wp-login-logo/\" target=\"_blank\">My WordPress Login</a> Logo Free WordPress Plugin</li>\n<li><a title=\"Erident Custom Login and Dashboard Plugin\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/erident-custom-login-and-dashboard/\" target=\"_blank\">Erident Custom Login and Dashboard</a> Free WordPress Plugin</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-custom-message-wordpress-login-page/\">Add Custom Message on WordPress Login Page</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-custom-message-wordpress-login-page/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"How to Reset or Change WordPress Password through phpMyAdmin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"http://smallenvelop.com/reset-wordpress-password-phpmyadmin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://smallenvelop.com/reset-wordpress-password-phpmyadmin/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 15 Jan 2015 16:33:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"WP Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WP Security\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"PhpMyAdmin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"security\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"WordPress password\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://smallenvelop.com/?p=1028\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:568:\"<p>In our daily life we all have many passwords. After all we  are human beings, so sometimes we forget our passwords. But what will happen if you forget your WordPress blog’s password or your site got .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/reset-wordpress-password-phpmyadmin/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/reset-wordpress-password-phpmyadmin/\">How to Reset or Change WordPress Password through phpMyAdmin</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3658:\"<p>In our daily life we all have many passwords. After all we  are human beings, so sometimes we forget our passwords.</p>\n<p>But what will happen if you forget your WordPress blog’s password or your site got hacked and you cannot reset your password using your email? It will be very difficult for you to login to admin dashboard.</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t worry guys you can reset your WordPress administrator password through PhpMyAdmin. This method will help you reset or change wordpress password.</p>\n<h2>Reset your WordPress Password through phpMyAdmin</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/change-wordpress-admin-password-smallenvelop.jpg\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-1148 aligncenter\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/change-wordpress-admin-password-smallenvelop.jpg\" alt=\"change wordpress admin password smallenvelop\" width=\"677\" height=\"346\" /></a></p>\n<p>Every WordPress Installation has MySQL Database which you can access via PhpMyAdmin.</p>\n<p>You will need to Know the exact name of your WordPress database but don&#8217;t get upset if you don&#8217;t know the name of  your WordPress database.</p>\n<p>Just go to  your root directory and edit <strong>wp-config.php</strong> file in any editor like Notepad++.  Here you will find your WordPress database name.</p>\n<p>Once you find the name of the database, follow the below steps to reset your WordPress password through phpMyadmin.</p>\n<ul class=\"list-group \"><li class=\"list-group-item\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></span> Open Your  cpanel, go to the databases section and click on phpMyAdmin.</li>\n<li class=\"list-group-item\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></span> Now, click on you WordPress database name and open the wp_users table.</li>\n<li class=\"list-group-item\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></span> In this table you will find “user_login” and “user_pass”. That is what we&#8217;re only looking for.  Now, you need to change your Password in “User_pass” section.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Note:- Because of security purposes you will not be able to enter plain text as password, you will need to encode your password with <strong>MD5 Hash</strong>.</p>\n<ul class=\"list-group \"><li class=\"list-group-item\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></span>  To convert Plain Text into MD5 hash, use this <a href=\"http://pajhome.org.uk/crypt/md5/\" target=\"_blank\">Javascript MD5 tool</a>. Just enter your text and convert. Once done, copy MD5 code and paste in “User_pass” section.</li>\n<li class=\"list-group-item\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></span> After pasting your password just save it.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Hurrey its all done you have successfully changed WordPress password throughPhpMyAdmin. I hope this article will help you.</p>\n<p>Here is a video tutorial by <a title=\"WPBeginner\" href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-reset-a-wordpress-password-from-phpmyadmin/\">WPbeginner</a></p>\n<p><span class=\'embed-youtube\' style=\'text-align:center; display: block;\'><iframe class=\'youtube-player\' type=\'text/html\' width=\'640\' height=\'390\' src=\'http://www.youtube.com/embed/MqPKyyQ6RbA?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;fs=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;wmode=transparent\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen=\'true\'></iframe></span></p>\n<p>For any queries please feel free to comment.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/reset-wordpress-password-phpmyadmin/\">How to Reset or Change WordPress Password through phpMyAdmin</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"http://smallenvelop.com/reset-wordpress-password-phpmyadmin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"How to Add Google Search in a WordPress Site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-google-search-in-wordpress-site/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-google-search-in-wordpress-site/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 07 Jan 2015 18:18:35 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"custom google search\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"google custom serach engine\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"google search\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"wordpress google search\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://smallenvelop.com/?p=1017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:587:\"<p>WordPress has  its own search function which comes in the form of WordPress Search Widget. But if  you are not satisfied with the funtionality of WordPress’s local search function, then here’s an alternative solution. You can use .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-google-search-in-wordpress-site/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-google-search-in-wordpress-site/\">How to Add Google Search in a WordPress Site</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3059:\"<p>WordPress has  its own search function which comes in the form of WordPress Search Widget. But if  you are not satisfied with the funtionality of WordPress’s local search function, then here’s an alternative solution. You can use the<strong> Custom Google  Search </strong> in your WordPress-based websites provided by Google itself.</p>\n<h2>Creating a Custom Google  Search Engine For Your WordPress</h2>\n<p>So lets start to create a custom google  search engine.</p>\n<h2>Step 1-</h2>\n<p>Sign in to <a title=\"custom search engine\" href=\"https://www.google.com/cse/\" target=\"_blank\">Custom Search Engine</a> with your google account.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1018\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/cse.png\" alt=\"cse\" width=\"640\" height=\"211\" /></p>\n<h2>Step 2-</h2>\n<p>Enter your WordPress site URL in sites to search section. This will automatically used as your search engine’s name in your Custom Google  Search Engine dashboard. Click on Create button to proceed to the next step.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1023\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Custom-Search-Create-CSE1.png\" alt=\"Custom Search - Create CSE\" width=\"522\" height=\"480\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Step 3-</h2>\n<p>On the next page, you will see a notification that you have successfully created your custom search engine. Here you will find 3 options for your custom google search engine first one is to GET THE CODE , second is PUBLIC URL and third is CONTROL PANEL.</p>\n<p>Click on &#8220;Get Code&#8221; button and on the page you will find the code for your google custom search engine. Copy the code you will need it in the next step.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1022\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/get-the-code.png\" alt=\"get the code\" width=\"640\" height=\"185\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Step 4-</h2>\n<p>Go to <strong>Appearance » Editor</strong> in your WordPress admin area and open <code>searchform.php</code> file  in the editor. Replace the existing serach form code with custom google search engine code that you copied  in the last step. Don&#8217;t worry if you can&#8217;t find searchform.php file just create a new one using a text editor like Notepad and upload it to your theme directory using FTP client and paste that code in it.</p>\n<h2>Step 5-</h2>\n<p>Go to <strong>Appearance » Widgets</strong> to drag and drop the search widget into your sidebar.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s all. Now you can see your custom google  search engine in your website.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1020\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/smallenvelop-search1.png\" alt=\"smallenvelop-search\" width=\"465\" height=\"464\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-google-search-in-wordpress-site/\">How to Add Google Search in a WordPress Site</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"http://smallenvelop.com/add-google-search-in-wordpress-site/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"5 Best Free WordPress Coupon Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"http://smallenvelop.com/5-best-free-wordpress-coupon-plugins/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"http://smallenvelop.com/5-best-free-wordpress-coupon-plugins/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 06 Jan 2015 17:24:23 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Best Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"coupon\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"coupon plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://smallenvelop.com/?p=1007\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:578:\"<p>WordPress coupon plugins are very helpful to turn your WordPress websites into a full featured coupon websites. Customers are always lookout for discount coupons or deals while purchasing products to save their money.  For increasing .. <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/5-best-free-wordpress-coupon-plugins/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/5-best-free-wordpress-coupon-plugins/\">5 Best Free WordPress Coupon Plugins</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Poonam\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4227:\"<p>WordPress coupon plugins are very helpful to turn your WordPress websites into a full featured coupon websites. Customers are always lookout for discount coupons or deals while purchasing products to save their money.  For increasing user engagement with your website and earn loyalty and money also this is an effective way to providing discounts to the users.  If you are ready  to offer discounts and coupons to your customers and this article will help you to create a wonderful coupon website.</p>\n<p>Here we are listing 5 best free WordPress coupon plugins that helps you to setup you website and increase your sales.</p>\n<h2>5 best free WordPress coupon plugins</h2>\n<h2><a title=\"coupon creator\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/coupon-creator/\" target=\"_blank\">1.Coupon Creator </a></h2>\n<p>coupon creator is one of the best free plugin for create coupons this plugin allows you to create your own coupons or upload an image of a coupon instead and display your coupons  on your site by using a shortcode.You can also create multiple coupons and assign them into categories.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1008\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/coupon-creator.png\" alt=\"coupon-creator\" width=\"620\" height=\"370\" /></p>\n<h2><a title=\"magic wp\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/magic-wp-coupons/\" target=\"_blank\">2.Magic WP Coupons &#8211; Lite</a></h2>\n<p>Magic WP Coupons easily lets you define stores and add coupons. This plugin will generate shortcodes for different stores or retailers and you can generate and use these shortcodes on your pages and posts, wherever you want to show discount coupons.</p>\n<p><a title=\"jc coupon\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/jaspreetchahals-coupons-lite/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1009\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/magic-wp-1024x463.png\" alt=\"magic wp\" width=\"640\" height=\"289\" /></a></p>\n<h2><a title=\"jc coupon\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/jaspreetchahals-coupons-lite/\" target=\"_blank\">3.JC Coupon</a></h2>\n<p>JC Coupon allows you to add Coupons on any post or page. You can set expiry date or custom text for expiry. You can set the expiry date of the coupon and after the expiry date, the coupon disappears automatically.This is must have affiliate tool where your URLs are masked and a click on your coupon will mean a hit to your your affiliate link.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1010\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/JC-coupon-lite.png\" alt=\"JC-coupon-lite\" width=\"620\" height=\"370\" /></p>\n<h2><a title=\"wps coupon\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wps-coupon-management/\" target=\"_blank\">4.NIC Discount Coupon Management</a></h2>\n<p>WPS coupon management gives you full functionality to manage discount coupons. It gives functionality like setting coupon expiry date, Auto coupon code generation or custom coupon code placement and coupon image selection. This plugin give you easy discount coupon management with auto scroll coupons loading view at front with shortcode.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1011\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/nic.jpg\" alt=\"nic\" width=\"770\" height=\"253\" /></p>\n<h2><a title=\"wp coupon widget\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-coupon-widget/\" target=\"_blank\">5.WordPress Coupon Widget</a></h2>\n<p>WordPress Coupon Widget shows coupons to your visitors instantly and also them to not only avail the coupon, but also subscribe to your email list. This plugin allows you to build your audience by increasing the number of subscribers who can be targeted later with emails for any of your products. This plugin also allows you to lock the coupons until a user share onto one’s social network.<br />\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1013\" src=\"http://smallenvelop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/WP-coupon-widget.png\" alt=\"WP-coupon-widget\" width=\"620\" height=\"370\" /></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com/5-best-free-wordpress-coupon-plugins/\">5 Best Free WordPress Coupon Plugins</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://smallenvelop.com\">SmallEnvelop</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"http://smallenvelop.com/5-best-free-wordpress-coupon-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:34:\"http://smallenvelop.com/blog/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";a:15:{s:4:\"date\";s